{
  "texts": [
    "The function should calculate and print the average rainfall.",
    "The daily rainfall amounts are occasionally corrupted, represented by negative values, so any negative value should be ignored from your calculation.",
    "The array also contains a special value, -999, to indicate the end of the valid rainfall data, so you should only examine values in the array up to the first occurrence of the value -999.",
    "Print the average of the valid rainfall data, rounded to 2 decimal places.",
    "If there are no valid rainfall values, then print \"no rain\"."
  ]
}